Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1} into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%grams} and shallot. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until the chicken is golden brown all over and the shallot is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Meanwhile, cut each @Plain Taco Tortillas{3.96}(cut into 8 triangles each) (2 per person) into 8 triangles (use scissors if easier).

Place on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer (use two trays if needed) and drizzle with @oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until lightly golden brown and crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them as they can brown quickly.

While the tortilla chips bake, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(grated) (or use a garlic press). Pop half the @Red Kidney Beans{1%carton} and their liquid into a #medium bowl{}, then mash with a #potato masher{}.

Add the garlic and @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to the chicken pan and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the remaining whole and mashed beans, @Chicken Stock Paste{20%grams}, @Tomato Puree{60%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{300%milliliters}.

Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down slightly and simmer, ~{5-7%minutes}.

When the soup has finished cooking, remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add a splash of water to loosen if needed until it's your desired consistency.

Share the chipotle chicken soup between your #bowls{}.

Drizzle with the @Soured Cream{75%grams} and swirl it in if you'd like.

Serve with the tortilla chips alongside for dipping. Enjoy!